  "text": "The mutation operator is restricted to a strategically chosen subset of the genes. This isolates the search process to the genes in highly fit solutions, facilitating the determination of the local optimum. The subset of genes is chosen by using a SVD process described in a previous paper by Martin [CITATION_1] . The subset of genes is chosen randomly from the set of all sets of highly correlated genes identified by SVD. The restriction only happened every other generation. This allows the mutation operators to have full access to the entire space of possible chromosomes.",
